curam.util.resources
Class StructCompare

java.lang.Object
  curam.util.resources.StructCompare

public class StructCompare
extends java.lang.Object

StructCompare is provided as a means of comparing Curam generated structures. This class is intended to making comparisons during testing easier since no .equals() exists for these structures.
Example of usage: 

 SomeStruct object1;
 SomeStruct object2;
 StructCompare compareObj1 = new StructCompare(object1);
 StructCompare compareObj2 = new StructCompare(object2);
 assertEquals(compareObj1, compareObj2);
or 
 compareObj1.equals(compareObj2);
or 
 compareObj1.equals(object2);
The .equals() of StructCompare will work with either another StructCompare instance or alternative an instance of the actual object being compared.

Method Detail

equals

public boolean equals(java.lang.Object compareToObjIn)
Compare the objects. This uses java reflection to compare the objects. First, if the object provided is an StructCompare instance, the actual object is retrieved. The public non-static fields of the structure are then compared. The structures are considered to be equal if they have the same identity, i.e. are the same object, or are both null.

The structures are considered to be different if they are of different classes, or if either, but not both, are null.

Otherwise, the structures are compared field by field and are considered to be equal if all their fields are equal. Fields are equal if they are both null, or if they are of "fundamental" types which compare equal.

Fields which are array types are compared element by element. Fields which are not fundamental types or array types are considered to be aggregates in their own right and are passed recursively to the equals() method.
